properties.areaDesc: Waters from Mexico Beach to Apalachicola FL from 20 to 60 NM; Waters from Suwannee River to Apalachicola FL from 20 to 60 NM; Waters from Okaloosa-Walton County Line to Mexico Beach from 20 to 60 NM
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 7 at 3:41AM EST until February 8 at 1:00AM EST by NWS Tallahassee FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, west winds 25 to 35 kt with gusts
up to 45 kt and seas 10 to 15 feet. For the Small Craft
Advisory, northwest winds 10 to 20 kt with gusts up to 25 kt
and seas 6 to 11 feet expected.

* WHERE...Offshore Gulf waters from the Walton-Okaloosa County
line to the Ochlockonee River from 20 to 60 nautical miles out.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, until 10 AM EST /9 AM CST/ this
morning. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 10 AM EST /9 AM
CST/ this morning to 1 AM EST /midnight CST/ Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.
